---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import CTA from "../components/CTA.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="FAQ | Cleanmail"
  description="Answers about Cleanmail: what it reads, how your data is handled, what it costs, and how it works for your whole family."
>
  <section class="faq">
    <p class="eyebrow">FAQ</p>
    <h1>Questions, answered.</h1>
    <p class="lede">The things parents ask most, especially about your privacy. If yours isn't here, just ask.</p>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Privacy and security</h2>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Can Cleanmail read my whole inbox?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">No. Cleanmail gets read-only access to Gmail, and it only ever reads mail from the senders you choose. Everyone else in your inbox stays untouched. Full details are in our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Do you sell my data or use it for ads?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Never. We do not sell your information, and we never use your email for advertising. You mean too much to us for that.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Are my emails stored somewhere?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Your raw emails are not kept. At digest time they're read, summarized, and then discarded. Only the short text summary is stored, never the original message.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Does the AI train on my email? Can a person read it?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">No to both. Your email goes to our AI provider only to write that one summary, and isn't kept there afterward. And no one at Cleanmail reads your mail, outside narrow security or legal exceptions.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">How is my data protected?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Everything is encrypted in transit and at rest, and your Google sign-in tokens are encrypted and never stored on your device. No one at Cleanmail reads your email. And before we could connect to Gmail at all, Cleanmail had to pass Google's CASA security assessment, the independent security review Google requires of any app that reads Gmail.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">How do I revoke access or delete everything?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Anytime. Disconnect Cleanmail from your <a href="https://myaccount.google.com/permissions">Google account permissions</a>, or delete your account in the app, which wipes your data and revokes Cleanmail's access to Google.</div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>How it works</h2>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">What can Cleanmail help me organize?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">The parent firehose: school, camp, sports, clubs, the newsletters and reminders and forms. You pick the senders that matter and Cleanmail handles the reading.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Does it work with any email account?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">We work with Google today, with plans to expand to more email providers soon.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Does Cleanmail send or delete my emails?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">No. It only reads. Cleanmail never sends, replies to, or deletes anything in your inbox.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">How does it get the dates onto my calendar?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">It reads each email, pulls out the events, and adds them to your Google Calendar automatically. It's a smart helper, not magic, so for anything critical it's worth a glance at the original, which is one tap away.</div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Your family, your inboxes</h2>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Can I track more than one kid?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Yes. Add up to eight people, each with their own activities, all in one digest.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Can I only put kids in the people section?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Nope! You can use Cleanmail for kids, a family section, work, anything you can think of where you want your email organized.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Can my partner and I share a digest?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Yes. Two parents can share one digest, so you're both looking at the same schedule.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Can I connect more than one inbox?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Yes. Link up to three Google inboxes and read them all in a single digest.</div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="faq-section">
      <h2>Plans and support</h2>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">How much does it cost?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">One flat plan at $6.99 a month, with a 14-day free trial. No tiers, no add-ons. See <a href="/subscriptions">Subscriptions</a> for the details.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">Do I need a card for the trial, and can I cancel?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">A card starts the trial, and you can cancel anytime from the app or the Stripe billing portal. Cancel before day 14 and you won't be charged.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">What devices does it run on?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Cleanmail is on iPhone today. Android is on our list.</div>
      </details>

      <details class="qa">
        <summary class="q">How do I get help?<svg class="chev" width="18" height="18" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"/></svg></summary>
        <div class="a">Email <a href="mailto:support@cleanmailapp.com">support@cleanmailapp.com</a> or visit our <a href="/support">Support</a> page. A real person reads every message.</div>
      </details>
    </div>

    <div class="final">
      <h2>Still have a question?</h2>
      <p>Cleanmail is coming to iPhone. Drop your email and we'll tell you the moment it's live.</p>
      <CTA />
    </div>

  </section>

  <style>
    .faq{max-width:760px;margin:0 auto;padding:80px 24px 90px}
    .eyebrow{text-align:center;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:1.5px;font-size:12.5px;font-weight:600;color:var(--purple);margin:0 0 14px}
    h1{text-align:center;font-size:clamp(30px,4.4vw,44px);font-weight:400;letter-spacing:-1px;color:var(--orange);margin:0 0 16px;line-height:1.08}
    .lede{text-align:center;max-width:540px;margin:0 auto;color:var(--ink);font-size:17px;line-height:1.55}

    .faq-section{margin-top:46px}
    .faq-section h2{font-size:19px;font-weight:600;color:var(--navy);margin:0 0 14px;letter-spacing:-.3px}

    details.qa{border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;background:#fff;margin-bottom:12px}
    details.qa[open]{box-shadow:0 10px 28px rgba(27,34,54,.05)}
    summary.q{list-style:none;cursor:pointer;display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:16px;padding:18px 20px;font-size:16px;font-weight:500;color:var(--navy)}
    summary.q::-webkit-details-marker{display:none}
    summary.q .chev{flex-shrink:0;color:var(--purple);transition:transform .2s}
    details.qa[open] summary.q .chev{transform:rotate(180deg)}
    .qa .a{padding:0 20px 18px;font-size:15px;line-height:1.6;color:var(--muted)}
    .qa .a a{color:var(--purple);text-decoration:underline}

    .final{text-align:center;margin-top:72px}
    .final h2{font-size:clamp(24px,3vw,32px);font-weight:500;color:var(--navy);margin:0 0 12px;letter-spacing:-.4px}
    .final p{font-size:16px;color:var(--muted);max-width:460px;margin:0 auto 26px;line-height:1.5}
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
